ions":["Adenocarcinoma","Leiomyosarcoma","Neuroendocrine carcinoma","Small cell carcinoma","Squamous cell carcinoma"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESquamous cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E of the oesophagus shows striking geographic variation, with particularly high rates in China, Central Asia, and parts of Africa. This variation is attributed to differences in risk factors including alcohol consumption, tobacco use, consumption of very hot beverages, and nutritional deficiencies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdenocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E is more prevalent in Western countries and is associated with gastro-oesophageal reflux disease and Barrett oesophagus. \u003Cstrong\u003ESmall cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eneuroendocrine carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E are relatively rare in the oesophagus and do not show significant geographic variation. \u003Cstrong\u003ELeiomyosarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E is an uncommon mesenchymal tumour that occurs at similar rates worldwide.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Squamous cell carcinoma of the oesophagus shows marked geographic variation with highest incidence in China","Risk factors for oesophageal squamous cell carcinoma include alcohol, smoking, hot beverages, and poor nutrition","Oesophageal adenocarcinoma is more common in Western countries and associated with Barrett oesophagus"],"references":["Zhu H, Ma X, Ye T, Wang H, Wang Z, Liu Q, Zhao K. Esophageal cancer in China: Practice and research in the new era. Int J Cancer. 2023 May 1;152(9):1741-1751. doi: 10.1002/ijc.34301. Epub 2022 Oct 5. PMID: 36151861.","Li J, Xu J, Zheng Y, Gao Y, He S, Li H, Zou K, Li N, Tian J, Chen W, He J. Esophageal cancer: Epidemiology, risk factors and screening. Chin J Cancer Res. 2021 Oct 31;33(5):535-547. doi: 10.21147/j.issn.1000-9604.2021.05.01. PMID: 34815628; PMCID: PMC8580797","Wang Y, Mukkamalla 